                            <comment id="17955612" author="JIRAUSER309899" created="Mon, 2 Jun 2025 08:15:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This defect is flagged due to commons-validator v1.9.0 used in kafka_2.13 v4.0.0 which uses commons-beanutils v1.9.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17957422" author="showuon" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 03:15:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve requested for a release in `commons-validator` project: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-validator/commit/e6c1c3e875a4913577245751c4814177cea758b3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-validator/commit/e6c1c3e875a4913577245751c4814177cea758b3&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17958610" author="fvaleri" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 07:55:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To me, it looks like Kafka is not vulnerable to CVE-2025-48734. In core we depend on commons-validator:1.7 that brings in the vulnerable commons-beanutils:1.9.4. From commons-validator, we only use InetAddressValidator in CoreUtils, which does not use PropertyUtilsBean and BeanUtils classes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17965208" author="showuon" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2025 02:56:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/19939&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/19939&lt;/a&gt; is to bump the `commons-beanutils` dependency version to 1.11.0 to resolve the CVE. After `commons-validator` has new release, we should remove this `commons-beanutils` version bump workaround in this PR. Closing this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
